      <section eId="sec_10_7_41">
        <num>10-7-41</num>
        <content>
          <p>Payment by a surety or endorser of a debt past due shall entitle him to proceed immediately against his principal for the sum paid, with interest thereon, and all legal costs to which he may have been subjected by the default of his principal.</p>
          <p>(Orig. Code 1863, § 2139; Code 1868, § 2134; Code 1873, § 2161; Code 1882, § 2161; Civil Code 1895, § 2980; Civil Code 1910, § 3552; Code 1933, § 103-302.)</p>
        </content>
